'''Claude Joli-Coeur''' is the 16th [[National Film Board of Canada#Government Film Commissioners|Government Film Commissioner and Chairperson]] of the [[National Film Board of Canada]]. He was appointed to the post on November 27 2014, after previously serving as interim Government Film Commissioner. A lawyer by training with a background in entertainment law as well as international co-productions, Joli-Coeur first joined the NFB in 2003, before becoming assistant commissioner in 2007.<ref name=G&M>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/film/national-film-board-of-canada-appoints-11-year-veteran-claude-joli-coeur-as-new-chair/article21891191/|title=National Film Board of Canada appoints 11-year veteran Claude Joli-Coeur as new chair|last=Houpt|first=Simon|date=2 December 2014|work=Globe and Mail|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/national-film-board-of-canada-appoints-claude-joli-coeur-as-new-chair-1201369256/|title=National Film Board of Canada Appoints Claude Joli-Coeur as New Chair|last=Zumberge|first=Marianne|date=2 December 2014|work=Variety|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lapresse.ca/cinema/nouvelles/201412/03/01-4824886-claude-joli-coeur-nouveau-president-de-lonf.php|title=Claude Joli-Coeur, nouveau président de l'ONF|date=3 December 2014|work=La Presse|publisher=The Canadian Press|language=French|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref>

On March 8, 2016, [[International Women's Day]], Joli-Coeur announced a new gender-parity initiative at the NFB that will see half of all its production spending committed to films directed by women.<ref name="Taylor March 8">{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/film/nfb-pledge-for-gender-parity-could-spur-change-in-canadian-film-industry/article29083931/|title=NFB pledge for gender parity could spur change in Canadian film industry|last=Taylor|first=Kate|authorlink=Kate Taylor (novelist)|work=[[The Globe and Mail]]|date=9 March 2016|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/canada-bankrolling-more-female-directors-873546|title=Canada Bankrolling More Female Directors to Close Gender Gap|last=Vlessing|first=Etan|date=8 March 2016|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref> On June 21, 2016, he received the "Please Adjust Your Set Award" from [[Women in Film and Television International|Women in Film + Television]] Vancouver, "which honours a person or organization that has made a major contribution to promote gender equality in film, television or screen based media."<ref name="Mullen">{{cite news|url=http://povmagazine.com/blog/view/mina-shum-claude-joli-coeur-receive-spotlight-awars-from-wiftv|title=Mina Shum, Claude Joli-Coeur Receive Spotlight Awards from WIFTV|last=Mullen|first=Pat|date=21 June 2016|work=Point of View|publisher=[[Documentary Organization of Canada]]|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref>

==Background==
Prior to joining the NFB, he worked for [[Astral Media| Astral Entertainment Group]], as Director of Business Affairs and then as Vice President of Legal and Business Affairs, from 1987 to 1995. In 1995, he was appointed Vice President, Legal and International Affairs, at {{Interlanguage link multi|Le Groupe Coscient|fr}}, a position he held for five years. From 2000 to 2002, he served as Vice President, Legal and Business Affairs, and Secretary at [[TVA (Canada)|TVA International]], as well as Vice President, Business Affairs, at {{Interlanguage link multi|Zone 3 (company)|fr|3=Zone 3|lt=Zone 3}}.<ref name=G&M/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://onf-nfb.gc.ca/en/about-the-nfb/organization/commissioner/|title=Government Film Commissioner and Chairperson of the NFB|work=National Film Board of Canada website|publisher=Government of Canada|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref> 

