{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Use British English|date=December 2015}} '''Henry Spry''' (born c. 1835) was a playwright and [[pantomime]] performer who co-wrote and appeared in nearly 50 productions with [[George Augustus Conquest|George Conquest]] at the [[Surrey Theatre]] and elsewhere.
==Early life== Henry Spry was born around 1835 in Bloomsbury, London.
==Family== Spry married Eliza. Spry's daughter Alice was an actress.<ref>http://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk/viewer/bl/0000053/18950928/030/0011</ref>
==Career== Spry was a playwright and pantomime performer who co-wrote and appeared in nearly 50 productions with George Conquest at the Surrey Theatre and elsewhere.<ref name="Law2013">"Conquest family" in {{cite book|author=Jonathan Law (Ed.)|title=The Methuen Drama Dictionary of the Theatre|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Tb-OAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA124|year=2011|publisher=Bloomsbury|location=London|isbn=978-1-4081-3148-0|page=124}}</ref><ref>Pickering, David, & John Morley. (1993) ''Encyclopedia of pantomime''. Gale Research International. {{ISBN|9781873477458}}</ref><ref name="Stephens">{{cite book|author=Stephens, John Russell|title=The Profession of the Playwright: British Theatre, 1800-1900|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4lbB2vNCEIAC&pg=PA9|year=2006|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge|isbn=978-0-521-03443-2|page=9}}</ref>
==Works with George Conquest== *''Spitz-Spitz the Spider Crab; or The Pirate of Spitsbergen''. Grecian Theatre, 1875. *''Jack and the Beanstalk, which grew to the moon; or, the Giant, Jack Frost and the Ha-Ha Balloon''. Surrey Theatre, 1886. Starring [[Dan Leno]] and wife. *''Sinbad and the Little Old Man of the Sea; or, The Tinker, the Tailor, the Soldier, the Sailor, Apothecary, Ploughboy, Gentleman Thief''. Surrey Theatre, 1887. Starring Dan Leno and wife.
