'''Sean Cody''' is a [[gay pornography]] studio founded in fall 2001.  The website predominantly features young, muscular, men in solo and hardcore bareback scenes. Sean Cody has a strict model selection, with contracts requiring no prior pornographic experience ('exclusive' men).

Sean Cody was run by the company Cody Media [[Incorporation (business)|Inc]] from 2003 until 2015 where it was sold to porn conglomerate [[MindGeek]] (who owns other competitor studios such as [[Men.com]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zoominfo.com/c/Cody-Media-Inc/28560195|title=Cody Media Inc|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref><ref name="queermenowscsale">{{cite web|title=Sean Cody Acquired by MindGeek (Men.com)|url=http://www.queermenow.net/blog/sean-cody-mencom/|website=www.queermenow.net|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref> This raised some considerable questions around the quality and exclusivity of the content, as the same parent company owned the content-sharing websites that have negatively affected many other studios. A 2014 article by internet magazine Slate explained how "MindGeek has become the porn monopoly, putting industry members in the paradoxical position of working for the very company that profits from the piracy of their work."<ref>{{cite news|last1=Auerbach|first1=David|title=Vampire Porn|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/technology/2014/10/mindgeek_porn_monopoly_its_dominance_is_a_cautionary_tale_for_other_industries.single.html|accessdate=26 July 2016|agency=Slate|date=23 October 2014}}</ref>

